Eh, Jens...

1169
01:28:51,026 --> 01:28:53,508
one thing I can tell you, man...

1170
01:28:53,890 --> 01:28:57,119
Our Hannes is lost for seafaring.

1171
01:28:59,209 --> 01:29:02,121
What love can do to an man...

1172
01:29:04,235 --> 01:29:06,971
I'm glad we're at sea again tomorrow.

1173
01:29:10,928 --> 01:29:14,258
Hey Jens, Fiete, it's almost 7
and you're not yet ready!

1174
01:29:14,378 --> 01:29:17,240
- I'll stay on board.
- You're both mad.

1175
01:29:17,360 --> 01:29:19,248
I want to stay in Hamburg forever.

1176
01:29:19,368 --> 01:29:22,539
Hamburg is the most beautiful city of
the world, not even Cologne can compete.

1177
01:29:22,659 --> 01:29:25,087
I'm sick and tired of Hamburg.

1178
01:29:25,956 --> 01:29:27,095
Owww....

1179
01:29:27,215 --> 01:29:29,091
Come, go ahead, get in!

1180
01:29:29,211 --> 01:29:31,064
and put it down there... so...

1181
01:29:31,184 --> 01:29:33,645
You... you couldn't find
any higher place to live?

1182
01:29:33,765 --> 01:29:36,342
You better be glad
that I'm no lighthouse keeper!

1183
01:29:36,462 --> 01:29:39,030
What's going on here?
Anyone's birthday?

1184
01:29:39,150 --> 01:29:42,089
Don't be so inquisitive, Mrs. Börgel...
Come here... here's 50 mark...

1185
01:29:42,209 --> 01:29:45,809
- There's nothing wrong in asking, no?
- Now don't stand around here...

1186
01:29:45,929 --> 01:29:48,149
better go to the kitchen,
Gisa will be here any moment!

1187
01:29:50,615 --> 01:29:52,282
Well good night, Mr. Wellenkamp,

1188
01:29:52,402 --> 01:29:54,854
I will unpack the new buscherumps
tomorrow, all right?

1189
01:29:54,974 --> 01:29:57,346
It's all right, girl,
there's no hurry.

1190
01:29:57,466 --> 01:30:00,458
But you better go now -
for sure he's already waiting!

1191
01:30:01,867 --> 01:30:04,274
For me no one is waiting...

1192
01:30:05,131 --> 01:30:09,664
Say, Mr. Wellenkamp...
where's that... Steckelhörnstreet?

1193
01:30:11,627 --> 01:30:14,598
A young lady is here...
she wants to see you.

1194
01:30:14,718 --> 01:30:17,208
- What young lady?
- I don't know her.

1195
01:30:17,328 --> 01:30:19,169
She hasn't been here before.

1196
01:30:24,002 --> 01:30:27,098
- Don't you want to put on
at least a little bit?    - Why?

1197
01:30:28,496 --> 01:30:30,433
What are <i>you</i> doing here?

1198
01:30:30,553 --> 01:30:32,600
I have to tell you something.

1199
01:30:32,981 --> 01:30:34,860
Yes? Please?

1200
01:30:48,490 --> 01:30:53,469
<i>You're lucky with the ladies, Bel Ami...</i>

1201
01:30:53,739 --> 01:30:57,437
<i>so lucky with the ladies, Bel Ami...</i>

1202
01:30:57,972 --> 01:31:00,672
<i>you're not handsome,
but you've got charme...</i>

1203
01:31:00,792 --> 01:31:02,469
<i>you're not smart...</i>

1204
01:31:04,512 --> 01:31:06,367
<i>you're no hero...</i>

1205
01:31:07,048 --> 01:31:07,858
So...

1206
01:31:14,342 --> 01:31:16,843
<i>just a man...</i>

1207
01:31:17,489 --> 01:31:19,720
<i>who appeals...</i>

1208
01:31:20,354 --> 01:31:25,861
<i>You fall in love every day anew</i>

1209
01:31:25,981 --> 01:31:29,200
<i>you kiss them all
and never remain faithful...</i>

1210
01:31:29,320 --> 01:31:32,617
<i>but the woman who loves you...</i>

1211
01:31:33,732 --> 01:31:34,953
Huh?

1212
01:31:35,353 --> 01:31:38,629
How can one marry in house
with such narrow doors?

1213
01:31:45,817 --> 01:31:48,605
<i>Bel Ami, Bel Ami...</i>

1214
01:31:48,725 --> 01:31:51,176
<i>Bel Ami... yep!</i>

1215
01:31:52,500 --> 01:31:53,498
Yes...

1216
01:31:54,731 --> 01:31:57,902
And I really thought
you had something going with him.

1217
01:31:58,606 --> 01:32:02,293
Then I wouldn't have come - no?

1218
01:32:02,413 --> 01:32:03,385
No.

1219
01:32:17,095 --> 01:32:20,136
I guess you haven't had
anything to eat yet, right?

1220
01:32:20,256 --> 01:32:23,013
Then... then I'll...
wait a moment.

1221
01:32:24,980 --> 01:32:26,962
Mrs. Kaasbohm?

1222
01:32:28,148 --> 01:32:31,283
Oh couldn't we have some more tea,
please, Mother Kaasbohm?

1223
01:32:31,403 --> 01:32:35,356
- Is this the new bride, from Sunday?
- Do you like her?

1224
01:32:35,450 --> 01:32:37,000
Beats me!

1225
01:32:51,597 --> 01:32:53,382
Young man...

1226
01:32:56,619 --> 01:32:58,357
Lil' one...

1227
01:33:00,752 --> 01:33:03,676
Hello... hello,
stay here, eh!

1228
01:33:22,762 --> 01:33:26,238
Carl Wellenkamp,
The House for the Sailor...

1229
01:33:26,473 --> 01:33:29,788
No, Hannes, she left here
at seven prompt.

1230
01:33:30,081 --> 01:33:34,144
Now what could have happened.
She's no small child anymore.

1231
01:33:34,264 --> 01:33:36,457
She probably has to do some shopping...

1232
01:33:36,577 --> 01:33:41,211
...I'm sure!
She asked me about the Steckelhörn!

1233
01:33:46,987 --> 01:33:49,129
What's the matter, Mr. Kröger?

1234
01:33:51,125 --> 01:33:52,288
Nothing...

1235
01:33:53,180 --> 01:33:54,801
Nothing at all...

1236
01:34:01,899 --> 01:34:04,005
WHO DARES WINS

1237
01:34:05,503 --> 01:34:08,177
When did it start for you?

1238
01:34:08,297 --> 01:34:10,610
Well... wait...

1239
01:34:11,743 --> 01:34:15,771
- Actually, already at the Bajazzo...
- What Bajazzo?

1240
01:34:16,381 --> 01:34:18,686
The gambling machine!

1241
01:34:18,806 --> 01:34:21,187
- At Mrs. Börgel, downstairs
at your place!  - Yes...

1242
01:34:21,307 --> 01:34:25,895
Don't you remember... back then...
when you shoved me?

1243
01:34:26,015 --> 01:34:30,091
I couldn't stand you then...
you were so cheeky!

1244
01:34:31,206 --> 01:34:33,989
And when did it start for you?

1245
01:34:34,109 --> 01:34:37,059
- Also at a slot machine...
- But you just said...

1246
01:34:37,179 --> 01:34:39,560
No - not at Mrs. Börgel's...

1247
01:34:40,241 --> 01:34:42,836
- At Blankenese...
- I see...

1248
01:34:59,899 --> 01:35:03,187
Never let it be said
that slot machines were no good.

1249
01:35:45,512 --> 01:35:47,350
Say that again...!

1250
01:35:47,470 --> 01:35:49,290
But I can say it only once...

1251
01:35:49,410 --> 01:35:53,024
- But I want to hear it once more...
- But I won't say it!

1252
01:35:56,010 --> 01:35:58,524
<i>[ Your own peaceful home
is a piece of paradise ]</i>

1253
01:36:04,157 --> 01:36:07,627
That's pretty!
Where did you get the necklace?

1254
01:36:08,143 --> 01:36:09,999
It's from...

1255
01:36:11,102 --> 01:36:12,570
from the South Sea.

1256
01:36:12,981 --> 01:36:14,002
Ah...

1257
01:36:23,583 --> 01:36:27,504
- I'll find me a room tomorrow.
- But nearby, okay?

1258
01:36:28,824 --> 01:36:31,430
I'm afraid of tomorrow anyway.

1259
01:36:31,994 --> 01:36:33,509
Why that?

1260
01:36:33,629 --> 01:36:37,031
Do you think I don't know you
anymore tomorrow?     - No.

1261
01:36:43,774 --> 01:36:47,379
No... it's just because of...

1262
01:36:47,625 --> 01:36:49,266
Maybe it will hurt him.

1263
01:36:49,386 --> 01:36:51,990
Why? You didn't have
anything going with him!

1264
01:36:52,110 --> 01:36:53,587
No, it's not that...

1265
01:36:54,373 --> 01:36:56,792
But he was so different
in the last few days...

1266
01:36:56,912 --> 01:36:59,449
Sometimes I almost had the feeling...

1267
01:36:59,754 --> 01:37:02,102
I had that feeling from the start.

1268
01:37:02,844 --> 01:37:05,522
- He never said anything, but...
- See?

1269
01:37:05,642 --> 01:37:08,334
Then you don't need
to have a bad conscience.

1270
01:37:08,557 --> 01:37:11,422
- I just feel so ungrateful.
- But why...?

1271
01:37:11,542 --> 01:37:14,486
You looked after for him all those weeks!

1272
01:37:15,662 --> 01:37:18,398
Seems to be mighty hard for you, eh?

1273
01:37:20,241 --> 01:37:22,754
Don't talk such nonsense...

1274
01:37:26,445 --> 01:37:29,568
Wait... I've got something for you!

1275
01:37:30,860 --> 01:37:33,913
- You always wanted to exchange
your tie!     - Too late!

1276
01:37:34,033 --> 01:37:35,768
That suit is ruined.

1277
01:37:37,843 --> 01:37:40,790
Do you perhaps think
I'm dependent on her?

1278
01:37:43,361 --> 01:37:46,215
Whether you think
that I'm dependent on her, eh?

1279
01:37:48,375 --> 01:37:51,169
I'm not dependent on her!

1280
01:37:52,085 --> 01:37:53,236
Bye.

1281
01:37:53,356 --> 01:37:56,478
- Where do you want to go?
- To Margot.   - Come here!

1282
01:38:03,996 --> 01:38:05,264
Come in!

1283
01:38:17,935 --> 01:38:23,677
<i>What use to me is a pretty girl</i>

1284
01:38:23,797 --> 01:38:26,944
<i>when others take a walk in there</i>

1285
01:38:27,064 --> 01:38:28,975
Get out of here, you...!

1286
01:38:29,095 --> 01:38:34,490
<i>and kiss away all of her beauty</i>

1287
01:38:34,610 --> 01:38:37,872
<i>and kiss away all of her...</i>

1288
01:38:37,992 --> 01:38:39,527
Get out!

1289
01:38:46,397 --> 01:38:47,959
What's the matter with you?

1290
01:38:49,309 --> 01:38:50,871
Leave me alone...

1291
01:39:06,558 --> 01:39:09,516
- What's with Hannes?
- Shut up!

1292
01:39:10,268 --> 01:39:11,289
There...

1293
01:39:13,262 --> 01:39:15,034
Engagement rings...

1294
01:39:24,384 --> 01:39:25,617
Hannes...

1295
01:39:26,909 --> 01:39:28,987
Never mind...

1296
01:39:33,378 --> 01:39:35,278
You have to get out of here.

1297
01:39:35,642 --> 01:39:38,342
Don't you want
to join up with us again?

1298
01:39:39,094 --> 01:39:41,830
But aren't you...
already complete?

1299
01:39:41,950 --> 01:39:45,918
- No, we're not!  - No?
- Well, Karl! from Cologne...

1300
01:39:46,038 --> 01:39:49,299
He'd like to stay here,
he likes Hamburg a lot,

1301
01:39:49,419 --> 01:39:52,477
- if he finds a replacement.
- All of a sudden?

1302
01:39:53,275 --> 01:39:56,680
- How come?
- Oh...

1303
01:39:59,029 --> 01:40:00,778
...old story.

1304
01:40:01,037 --> 01:40:04,219
Ah... because of a woman.

1305
01:40:13,071 --> 01:40:14,257
No...

1306
01:40:17,873 --> 01:40:21,689
- No.   - The captain has a telephone,
I could get it straight quickly!

1307
01:40:23,392 --> 01:40:25,306
Back to sea...

1308
01:40:27,079 --> 01:40:29,064
At sea again...

1309
01:40:43,584 --> 01:40:48,871
<i>They celebrate a wedding...</i>

1310
01:40:48,991 --> 01:40:53,180
<i>but I don't care at all...</i>

1311
01:40:53,858 --> 01:40:57,850
<i>because I am a sailor...</i>

1312
01:40:58,132 --> 01:40:59,599
Good evening, dad!

1313
01:40:59,719 --> 01:41:02,335
<i>who does not...</i>

1314
01:41:13,319 --> 01:41:14,516
Jens!

1315
01:41:14,801 --> 01:41:16,586
What's wrong with you?

1316
01:41:17,255 --> 01:41:19,674
I cannot forget Margot.

1317
01:41:19,794 --> 01:41:22,081
Have you lost your marbles, eh?

1318
01:41:25,437 --> 01:41:28,349
You're crying... because of a woman?

1319
01:41:29,159 --> 01:41:31,014
Let her go!

1320
01:41:31,331 --> 01:41:35,358
<i>'Cause you are a sailor...</i>

1321
01:41:35,478 --> 01:41:39,794
<i>who does not know of faith...</i>

1322
01:41:39,914 --> 01:41:41,496
Hey, tomorrow...

1323
01:41:41,616 --> 01:41:44,807
you will be on sea again and then
everything will look different!

1324
01:41:45,184 --> 01:41:48,612
You... <i>always keep sailing...</i>

1325
01:41:49,156 --> 01:41:53,747
<i>under the heaven so hot...</i>

1326
01:41:55,368 --> 01:41:59,325
And when you're standing
up there on the yard again,

1327
01:42:00,011 --> 01:42:04,367
and the wind howls
in your ears up there, eh!

1328
01:42:05,189 --> 01:42:07,526
then you'll forget everything...

1329
01:42:07,878 --> 01:42:12,261
Jens, don't you remember
what our captain back then

1330
01:42:12,381 --> 01:42:15,642
wrote into our fleet calendar
for christmas?

1331
01:42:16,609 --> 01:42:21,611
"One wouldn't believe
what a man can forget...

1332
01:42:21,731 --> 01:42:23,361
...if he's a man"?

1333
01:42:23,481 --> 01:42:27,711
<i>My bride is the sea...</i>

1334
01:42:27,831 --> 01:42:31,961
And when you come home again
after such a long voyage,

1335
01:42:32,413 --> 01:42:35,571
then perhaps you no longer know

1336
01:42:36,029 --> 01:42:39,141
how she looked like... or...

1337
01:42:40,820 --> 01:42:43,213
...you find another.

1338
01:42:44,557 --> 01:42:46,271
If you want.

1339
01:42:53,458 --> 01:42:59,317
<i>What use is the crown to the emperor?</i>

1340
01:42:59,728 --> 01:43:04,162
<i>What use is his money to the sailor?</i>

1341
01:43:04,514 --> 01:43:09,082
<i>'cause there can't be anything better</i>

1342
01:43:09,387 --> 01:43:13,605
<i>than in Hamburg for the money a girl!</i>

1343
01:43:13,841 --> 01:43:15,179
Jens, sing along, eh!

1344
01:43:15,299 --> 01:43:20,194
<i>'cause there can't be anything better</i>

1345
01:43:20,414 --> 01:43:25,838
<i>than in Hamburg for the money a girl!</i>

1346
01:43:27,083 --> 01:43:28,638
Two, three -

1347
01:43:28,758 --> 01:43:32,607
<i>Hammonia...</i>

1348
01:43:32,727 --> 01:43:36,263
<i>Hammonia!</i>

1349
01:43:36,991 --> 01:43:45,557
<i>oh how glorious
are you standing there.</i>

1350
01:43:45,792 --> 01:43:52,239
<i>City of Hamburg,
at the Elbe's meadows</i>

1351
01:43:52,359 --> 01:43:54,616
- <i>how stately are you...</i>
- Hannes, here's the kitbag...

1352
01:43:54,736 --> 01:43:57,352
- Mrs. Börgel's got the keys
to your place.    - Fine.

1353
01:43:57,472 --> 01:43:58,902
What the...

1354
01:43:59,243 --> 01:44:02,911
- Hannes goes to sea again?
- Sure, dude! On our Padua!

1355
01:44:03,031 --> 01:44:05,988
- In place of Karl! The captain agreed!
- Hannes!

1356
01:44:06,108 --> 01:44:08,418
Sure, Anita...

1357
01:44:09,270 --> 01:44:12,722
once it has to be again...

1358
01:44:12,980 --> 01:44:15,998
now don't cry my girl, come...

1359
01:44:17,231 --> 01:44:19,250
come, give me a kiss...

1360
01:44:22,481 --> 01:44:26,403
you were... sure enough
not too bad...

1361
01:44:27,682 --> 01:44:28,516
Well...

1362
01:44:30,161 --> 01:44:31,828
...so let's go.

1363
01:44:42,251 --> 01:44:47,006
<i>...and you my love will stay here...</i>

1364
01:45:20,187 --> 01:45:21,772
Fine weather...

1365
01:45:21,892 --> 01:45:24,349
and a good trip, lad!

1366
01:45:45,300 --> 01:45:47,000
<i>Translation + subtitles:
Kurosuke@Karagarga</i>

1367
